# No Unapproved Status Changes

## Read operations

Freely query, list, summarize, and draft content for ADO and Polarion work items.

## Write operations — require confirmation

Before calling any of these, **show the proposed change and get explicit user approval**:

- ADO: `wit_create_work_item`, `wit_update_work_item`, `wit_update_work_items_batch`, state/field changes
- Polarion: `set_work_item_status`, `add_work_item_link`, `remove_work_item_link`, `add_reviewer`, `remove_reviewer`, `reset_review_status`, `create_test_result_record`, `add_work_item_comment` (when posting on behalf of user)

## Exceptions

- User explicitly says: "create", "update", "close", "link", "approve", "post comment", or "apply changes"
- User is iterating on a draft in chat and says "looks good, do it"

## Comments on Waiting state

When recommending Waiting, always draft the blocker comment for user approval:

> Blocked: [reason]. Waiting on: [person/team]. Expected resolution: [date if known].
